CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1962, pg. 1 reads: "At Woods Funeral - Shown above are scenes as Emmett Woods, dynamic civil rights fighter in Pittsburgh area, was carried to a final resting place after being stricken fatally last Friday at West Penn Hospital after a brief illness.  The funeral was held at Homestead's Second Baptist Church, with the Rev. O.C. Perkins presiding. - Harris Photo.""
TitMainTitle: Male pallbearers carrying flag draped casket of Emmett Woods out of Second Baptist Church, surrounded by women holding floral arrangements, Homestead
